    "text": "The direct comparison in A treats the LSOG continuous probability product as a binary map by applying a spatial threshold, enabling a pixel‑wise comparison with the Hagan et al. (2026) LiDAR classification.",
    "topic": "Thresholding for binary comparison"
  },
  {
    "text": "The apples‑to‑apples comparison in B uses post‑stratification of the model‑based LiDAR map to estimate design‑based quantities (e.g., area and accuracy) that are comparable with the LSOG design‑based estimates.",
    "topic": "Post‑stratification reconciliation"
  },
  {
    "text": "A and B are not contradictory if the direct comparison in A is restricted to visual or qualitative overlay, while B provides the formal inferential framework to evaluate statistical agreement.",
    "topic": "Overlay vs. inferential comparison"
  },
  {
    "text": "The Hagan et al. LiDAR map is reclassified to match the LSOG probability map’s definition of presence (e.g., aggregating multi‑class labels into a binary presence/absence) before the direct comparison.",
    "topic": "Harmonization of class definitions"
  }
]
